that the equations of motion really

2828
01:48:57,010 --> 01:48:58,990
do reflect the symmetry of the problem,

2829
01:48:59,190 --> 01:49:02,710
the symmetry being Lorentz invariance.

2830
01:49:03,290 --> 01:49:03,850
Now,

2831
01:49:03,850 --> 01:49:04,810
there is another symmetry.

2832
01:49:04,810 --> 01:49:07,570
The other symmetry is called Gagin invariance,

2833
01:49:07,570 --> 01:49:08,810
and we haven't gotten to it yet.

2834
01:49:08,810 --> 01:49:10,030
We'll get to it next time.

2835
01:49:17,429 --> 01:49:17,850
But,

2836
01:49:17,850 --> 01:49:20,230
and I'll tell you what it is next time,

2837
01:49:20,330 --> 01:49:25,190
but let me say that the three really

2838
01:49:25,190 --> 01:49:30,050
fundamental principles that come time and time again,

2839
01:49:30,610 --> 01:49:32,570
which we'll see in this simple example,

2840
01:49:34,630 --> 01:49:35,470
three principles

2841
01:49:37,570 --> 01:49:39,510
The first principle is called locality.

2842
01:49:45,250 --> 01:49:50,100
What locality says is that the way a thing changes only

2843
01:49:50,100 --> 01:49:54,950
depends on what's going on nearby the thing that you're thinking about.

2844
01:49:55,830 --> 01:49:58,900
A field over here doesn't change due

2845
01:49:58,900 --> 01:50:01,970
to a field over there having some value.

2846
01:50:02,130 --> 01:50:04,750
It changes because the field nearby has some value.

2847
01:50:05,070 --> 01:50:06,310
The motion of a particle only

2848
01:50:06,310 --> 01:50:07,550
changes when it's close to the field.

2849
01:50:07,550 --> 01:50:09,870
It only depends on the values of the fields nearby.

2850
01:50:10,670 --> 01:50:13,370
It also doesn't depend on the values of the

2851
01:50:13,370 --> 01:50:16,070
fields at a later time or an earlier time.

2852
01:50:16,570 --> 01:50:19,840
The equations of motion are

2853
01:50:19,840 --> 01:50:23,110
equations between things at a nearby,

2854
01:50:23,110 --> 01:50:25,610
in a small vicinity of the time,

2855
01:50:26,550 --> 01:50:28,310
being related to other things in

2856
01:50:28,310 --> 01:50:30,070
the same small vicinity of time.

2857
01:50:31,390 --> 01:50:32,410
And space.

2858
01:50:33,210 --> 01:50:34,490
How do we represent,

2859
01:50:34,490 --> 01:50:36,130
how do we implement that?

2860
01:50:36,130 --> 01:50:37,730
We implement that,

2861
01:50:37,730 --> 01:50:38,670
that's called locality.

2862
01:50:39,130 --> 01:50:41,950
We implement that by making the action,

2863
01:50:45,650 --> 01:50:48,380
the action should be an

2864
01:50:48,380 --> 01:50:51,110
integral over all space and time,

2865
01:50:51,110 --> 01:50:51,530
dx,

2866
01:50:51,530 --> 01:50:51,950
dt,

2867
01:50:52,689 --> 01:50:55,050
of some kind of Lagrange density,

2868
01:50:55,290 --> 01:50:58,460
which only depends on the values of

2869
01:50:58,460 --> 01:51:01,630
things at a particular point in the neighborhood,

2870
01:51:01,930 --> 01:51:03,230
let's call it x and t,

2871
01:51:04,650 --> 01:51:05,330
and,

2872
01:51:05,330 --> 01:51:06,010
well,

2873
01:51:06,130 --> 01:51:07,330
sorry,

2874
01:51:08,150 --> 01:51:10,870
depends on things and derivatives.

2875
01:51:12,230 --> 01:51:15,910
Let's say fields and their derivatives.

2876
01:51:17,610 --> 01:51:18,850
In other words,

2877
01:51:18,850 --> 01:51:21,100
it depends on data which has

2878
01:51:21,100 --> 01:51:23,350
to do with local nearby concepts.

2879
01:51:23,830 --> 01:51:27,140
And you add up the action in

2880
01:51:27,140 --> 01:51:30,450
point by point by point in space,

2881
01:51:32,990 --> 01:51:36,030
and what comes out is differential.

2882
01:51:36,870 --> 01:51:39,970
Differential equations are equations which relate how things

2883
01:51:39,970 --> 01:51:43,070
change from one point to another to neighboring things.

2884
01:51:43,750 --> 01:51:47,530
You could imagine the action not having this form.

2885
01:51:47,750 --> 01:51:51,840
You could imagine the action has in it things which involve

2886
01:51:51,840 --> 01:51:55,930
products of fields over here and products of fields far away.

2887
01:51:56,790 --> 01:51:58,290
But then your equations,

2888
01:51:58,290 --> 01:52:00,610
when you worked out the Euler-Lagrange equations,

2889
01:52:00,890 --> 01:52:03,490
they would have the form that the way

2890
01:52:03,490 --> 01:52:06,090
things change over here depends on what's happening.

2891
01:52:06,110 --> 01:52:07,090
What's going on over here.

2892
01:52:07,710 --> 01:52:08,310
No,

2893
01:52:08,310 --> 01:52:11,170
that's not the way the action principle works.

2894
01:52:11,430 --> 01:52:14,870
The action depends on fields and neighboring fields.

2895
01:52:15,390 --> 01:52:17,270
Neighboring fields now means derivatives.

2896
01:52:18,090 --> 01:52:21,350
So the way the field changes at one point is only determined

2897
01:52:21,350 --> 01:52:24,610
by the value of the field at that point and neighboring points.

2898
01:52:25,070 --> 01:52:28,910
So that phi sub u is four components derivative?

2899
01:52:29,230 --> 01:52:29,410
Yes,

2900
01:52:29,410 --> 01:52:30,330
four components.

2901
01:52:30,710 --> 01:52:31,930
Four components.

2902
01:52:32,170 --> 01:52:35,770
Phi sub mu represents the four derivatives of phi.

2903
01:52:37,669 --> 01:52:39,010
And as I said,

2904
01:52:39,010 --> 01:52:43,140
it says that fields change in a way which depends

2905
01:52:43,140 --> 01:52:47,270
only on what's going on nearby in space and time.

2906
01:52:48,070 --> 01:52:49,910
That's the principle of locality,

2907
01:52:49,910 --> 01:52:52,060
and it's no more and no less

2908
01:52:52,060 --> 01:52:54,210
than saying that the action is an integral.

2909
01:52:55,030 --> 01:52:57,290
How do you quantify nearby?

2910
01:52:57,890 --> 01:52:58,310
Well,

2911
01:52:58,310 --> 01:52:59,910
by making derivatives.

2912
01:53:00,190 --> 01:53:03,230
By saying it depends on fields and their first derivatives.

2913
01:53:03,790 --> 01:53:04,470
That's all.

2914
01:53:04,470 --> 01:53:06,550
Fields and their first derivatives.

2915
01:53:06,970 --> 01:53:07,570
Now,

2916
01:53:07,570 --> 01:53:09,230
you could try putting in second derivatives,

2917
01:53:09,230 --> 01:53:12,290
and there's an interesting subject there,

2918
01:53:12,290 --> 01:53:16,430
but let's not get into it too much.

2919
01:53:17,990 --> 01:53:20,700
Action principle together with the idea that the

2920
01:53:20,700 --> 01:53:23,410
action is built up out of incremental pieces,

2921
01:53:24,070 --> 01:53:26,370
each of which depends only on a

2922
01:53:26,370 --> 01:53:28,670
field in a neighborhood and its local neighbors.

2923
01:53:29,470 --> 01:53:31,940
What we've been doing here

2924
01:53:31,940 --> 01:53:34,410
just depends on x and y.

2925
01:53:35,230 --> 01:53:35,850
Yeah,

2926
01:53:35,850 --> 01:53:37,510
when we're talking about the particle,

2927
01:53:37,510 --> 01:53:37,810
yes,

2928
01:53:37,810 --> 01:53:39,890
when we're talking about the particle motion,

2929
01:53:40,590 --> 01:53:43,360
then we can substitute the statement that the

2930
01:53:43,360 --> 01:53:46,130
Lagrangian along the world line of a particle

2931
01:53:46,130 --> 01:53:49,020
only depends on the positions of the

2932
01:53:49,020 --> 01:53:51,910
particles and neighboring positions along the world line.

2933
01:53:52,190 --> 01:53:53,210
But also,

2934
01:53:53,210 --> 01:53:55,240
it depends on the values of the

2935
01:53:55,240 --> 01:53:57,270
fields at the position of the particle.

2936
01:53:57,770 --> 01:54:00,320
The acceleration of a particle over here does not

2937
01:54:00,320 --> 01:54:02,870
depend on the value of the field over here.

2938
01:54:02,870 --> 01:54:04,230
It depends on the values of

2939
01:54:04,230 --> 01:54:05,590
the fields in the neighboring region.

2940
01:54:06,530 --> 01:54:08,570
That's the principle of locality.

2941
01:54:09,410 --> 01:54:13,680
That the response of either fields or particles

2942
01:54:13,680 --> 01:54:17,950
depends only on what's going on infinitesimally close by.

2943
01:54:18,949 --> 01:54:19,650
Second,

2944
01:54:19,650 --> 01:54:21,290
Lorentz invariants.

2945
01:54:25,640 --> 01:54:29,245
Lorentz invariants are in both cases

2946
01:54:29,245 --> 01:54:32,850
for both the particle and the region.

2947
01:54:32,870 --> 01:54:37,690
The rule is build the Lagrangian out of scalars.

2948
01:54:38,710 --> 01:54:40,270
Build the Lagrangian,

2949
01:54:40,270 --> 01:54:43,150
make sure that the Lagrangian itself is a scalar.

2950
01:54:43,550 --> 01:54:48,050
That's another way of saying that we'll all agree about

2951
01:54:48,050 --> 01:54:52,550
the action within a certain volume of space and time.

2952
01:54:54,010 --> 01:54:55,350
Lorentz invariants,

2953
01:54:55,350 --> 01:54:57,650
L equals scalar.

2954
01:55:02,950 --> 01:55:05,290
Those two principles are very pervasive.

2955
01:55:05,550 --> 01:55:07,140
There is one more principle

2956
01:55:07,140 --> 01:55:08,730
which we haven't worked out yet.

2957
01:55:08,830 --> 01:55:09,920
I have it in my notes

2958
01:55:09,920 --> 01:55:11,010
and so I'll write it down,

2959
01:55:11,010 --> 01:55:13,150
but it's going to be the subject of next week.

2960
01:55:13,610 --> 01:55:14,830
Gauge invariants.

2961
01:55:20,530 --> 01:55:22,310
And that means...

2962
01:55:23,810 --> 01:55:25,050
We'll find out next week.

2963
01:55:27,490 --> 01:55:31,010
These three principles are extremely pervasive.

2964
01:55:31,010 --> 01:55:33,050
Every theory that we know about,

2965
01:55:33,050 --> 01:55:35,190
whether it's general relativity,

2966
01:55:35,190 --> 01:55:37,030
quantum electrodynamics,

2967
01:55:37,030 --> 01:55:39,050
the standard model of particle physics,

2968
01:55:39,050 --> 01:55:40,890
Yang-Mills theory,

2969
01:55:40,890 --> 01:55:45,910
all conform to these three principles.

2970
01:55:46,789 --> 01:55:50,609
And basically I would say anything else on top

2971
01:55:50,609 --> 01:55:54,430
of that that you need is sort of incidental.

2972
01:55:54,430 --> 01:55:57,230
And incidental not in the sense that it's not important.

2973
01:55:57,790 --> 01:55:59,470
But incidental in the sense...

2974
01:55:59,470 --> 01:56:00,730
Or what's the right word?

2975
01:56:00,910 --> 01:56:04,920
That it varies from example to example in ways

2976
01:56:04,920 --> 01:56:08,930
that don't really have to do with such deep principles.

2977
01:56:09,230 --> 01:56:09,790
The fact,

2978
01:56:09,790 --> 01:56:10,310
for example,

2979
01:56:10,310 --> 01:56:13,010
that the standard model has three species of quarks,

2980
01:56:13,010 --> 01:56:15,270
well that's not contained in here.

2981
01:56:15,870 --> 01:56:18,590
That's a sort of random addition.

2982
01:56:18,850 --> 01:56:21,410
But the basic deep principles are these.

2983
01:56:23,010 --> 01:56:25,930
So next time we'll learn what gauge invariance is.

2984
01:56:27,890 --> 01:56:28,890
As I said,

2985
01:56:28,890 --> 01:56:29,450
I advise you to...

2986
01:56:29,470 --> 01:56:32,800
Go through these equations and figure

2987
01:56:32,800 --> 01:56:36,130
out where the various things came from.

2988
01:56:36,310 --> 01:56:38,450
Because I certainly don't expect that

2989
01:56:38,450 --> 01:56:40,590
you got it all in one sitting.

2990
01:56:42,950 --> 01:56:43,950
For more,

2991
01:56:43,950 --> 01:56:46,370
please visit us at stanford.edu.

